        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 3:31PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gardnerville, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gardnerville, Gardnerville Ranchos, Johnson Lane, Indian Hills,
Genoa, Kingsbury, Junction U.S 395 And NV 756, Us 395 At
Douglas-Carson City Co Line, Gardnerville Ranch, Stewart,
Minden-Tahoe Airport, Junction Nv 88 And Nv 756, Junction Nv 88 And
Nv 206, Minden, and Heavenly Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
